nd as a master of modern Polish prose only after Communism ended. He remains to be discovered in the English-speaking world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, Polish. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zFrance. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aDrabik, Grazyna.1 aDrabik, Grażyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelstein, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelstein, Laura.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300190045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300190045.jpg  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019